  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In this study safety and efficacy of oral morphine sulphate is evaluated in order to reduce
      opioids administration during major urological surgery
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The administration of oral morphine sulfate could be useful to reduce the use of opioids in
      major urological surgery. This study aims to assess the safety and efficacy of two different
      oral morphine sulphate doses 0,2 mg/kg vs 0,4mg/kg in major urological surgery.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
